---
By: Thomas More
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 252
    Verse: 14
Tags:
  - Humility
---
To be humble to superiors, is duty; to equals, is courtesy; to inferiors,
is nobleness; and to all, safety; it being a virtue that, for all its
lowliness, commandeth those it stoops to.
